AIM

To demonstrate various data types and operators in Python such as arithmetic identities, bitwise operators, addition and subtraction properties.

Algorithm
Start the program now.
We need to assign two integer variables: a is 208 and b is 600.
Next we have to print the heading that says we are going to verify some equations.
We will use Python to verify some algebra things and print the results.
Then we need to print the heading for the part about bitwise operators.
Now we do some bitwise operations using the or. And xor operators and we check how they are related to each other.
After that we print the heading for the part about addition.
We will verify that addition works correctly using bitwise operators.
Next we print the heading for the part, about subtraction.
We will use bitwise expressions to verify that subtraction works correctly.
Finally we display the results of all the expressions we did.
The program ends here.

SOURCE CODE
a = 208
b = 600

print("In equation Assignment operators:\n")

print((a+b)**2 == a**2 + 2*(a*b) + b**2)
print((a-b)**2 == a**2 - 2*(a*b) + b**2)
print((a+b)*(a+b) == 2*(a**2 - b**2))
print((a+b)+(a-b) == a*2)
print((a**3 + b**3) == (a+b)*(a**2 - a*b + b**2))

print("In Bitwise operators")

print(a | b == (a ^ b) + (a & b))
print(a ^ (a & b) == (a | b) ^ b)
print(b ^ (a & b) == (a | b) ^ a)
print((a & b) ^ (a | b) == a ^ b)

print("In Addition\n")

print((a+b) == (a|b) + (a&b))
print(a+b == (a^b) + 2*(a&b))

print("In Subtraction\n")

print(a-b == (a ^ (a & b)) - ((a | b) ^ a))
print(a-b == ((a | b) ^ b) - (b ^ (a & b)))
print(a-b == (a ^ (a & b)) - (b ^ (a & b)))
print(a-b == ((a | b) ^ b) - ((a | b) ^ a))


